sentences: Lionel Loueke (born 27 April 1973) is a guitarist and vocalist born in Benin.
He moved to Ivory Coast in 1990 to study at the National Institute of Art.

He studied at the National Institute of Art in Ivory Coast, the American School of Music in Paris from 1994 to 1998, Berklee College of Music from 1999 to 2001, and the Thelonious Monk Institute from 2001 to 2003.

His album Mwaliko (2010) is a collection of duo and trio performances that combines traditional West African music with jazz.
In early 2008, Loueke's "Kponnon Kpété" won Best Traditional World Song in the 7th Annual Independent Music Awards.
